briefdescription.para: Dataset ID (DSID), a unique identifier for the dataset. Initialized to 0.
Flag indicating if this is Monte Carlo data (true) or real data (false). Initialized to true.
Format of the derived data (e.g., "DAOD_PHYS"). Initialized empty.
Map of input files, keyed by an index. Initialized empty.
General configuration settings as key-value pairs. Initialized empty.
ATLAS Metadata Interface tag. Initialized empty.
Information about Monte Carlo generators used. Initialized empty.
Range information for input data, possibly event ranges. Initialized empty.
Number of events, reserved for ROOT mapping. Initialized to -1.
Free parameter for event indexing. Initialized to -1.
Flag indicating if metadata was found. Initialized to false.
Human-readable name of the dataset. Initialized empty.
Total size of the dataset, potentially in bytes. Initialized to 0.
Theoretical correction factor. Initialized to 0.
Center-of-mass energy of the collision, typically in GeV. Initialized to 0.

Processing completion percentage. Initialized to 0.
Energy of the colliding beams. Initialized to 0.
Cross-section of the physics process. Initialized to 0.
Mean value of the cross-section. Initialized to 0.
Integrated luminosity of the data-taking campaign. Initialized to 0.
Number of files in the dataset. Initialized to 0.
Total number of events across all files. Initialized to 0.

Main structure for storing metadata about physics datasets.

detaileddescription.para: Contains comprehensive information about physics datasets, including identifiers, Monte Carlo simulation parameters, cross-sections, event counts, and other properties necessary for proper data handling and normalization in physics analyses.
